From: ASCEND Curriculum Maintainer
Subject: [PATCH] Sort module sessions alphabetically; remove week designation from list views

Sessions inside each module were grouped under "Week 1 / Week 2 / ..." headers
using a `week` field from source data that does not reflect the live academic
calendar. This produced misleading schedules every time the real calendar
shifted.

This patch:
  1. Sorts sessions alphabetically by title in both the desktop and mobile
     module session lists.
  2. Removes the "Week N" group headers and the mobile left-rail week column.
  3. Strips "Week N" / "Wk N" from every session subtitle / breadcrumb / list
     eyebrow so nothing in a list view implies a schedule.

Deliberately preserved:
  - The "Week" StatTile on the session detail card (a data field, not a list).
  - The "Week" facet in global search filters (user-driven filter, not display).
  - The "Week" column in the alignment-audit CSV export.
  - The "Week" DetailRow inside the session detail body.
